# Gitleaks false-positive suppressions.
#
# Each entry is a gitleaks "fingerprint" (commit:file:rule:line) for a finding
# that has been reviewed and confirmed NOT to be a real secret. Fingerprints are
# printed by the hmcts/secrets-scanner job output. This file is honoured by
# gitleaks regardless of which config the scanner loads via GITLEAKS_CONFIG.
#
# Before adding a line here, confirm the value is genuinely not sensitive.

# --- gradle.properties: apiSpecVersion release-version strings ---------------
# `apiSpecVersion` is a build version (e.g. 0.1.27-SPRDT-848). The ticket suffix
# makes the value look high-entropy, so the generic-api-key rule flags it. It is
# a published artifact version, not a credential.
6d881cd5308eca060590529de15d5fd56aa423d1:gradle.properties:generic-api-key:10
4921c9a215ac6705098cbfaa6d43eda90cc5e17f:gradle.properties:generic-api-key:10

# --- Azurite emulator development key -----------------------------------------
# docker/integration-azurite-storage.env holds the PUBLIC, Microsoft-documented
# default account key for the Azurite blob emulator account `devstoreaccount1`.
# It is not a production secret (see docker/README.md). The inline `gitleaks:allow`
# in that file does not apply because the key is read by a custom .env parser that
# would treat a trailing comment as part of the value, so we suppress by fingerprint.
246454de965fecbd5bc89c73f07af4d7ed2aeb75:docker/integration-azurite-storage.env:generic-api-key:7
